Interface Thermostat


  • public interface Thermostat
    The main interface for interacting with the thermostat.
    Author:
    Mike Kelly (pioto@pioto.org)

    • Method Detail

      • getTemperature

        Float getTemperature()
        Gets the ambient temperature recorded by the thermostat.
        Returns:
        The current temperature in degrees Fahrenheit. If this cannot be read, null will be returned.

      • getOperatingMode

        OperatingMode getOperatingMode()
        Returns the current operating mode of the thermostat. This is whether it is trying to heat or cool the room.
        Returns:
        the current operating mode. If this cannot be read, null will be returned.

      • setOperatingMode

        void setOperatingMode(OperatingMode tmode)
                      throws NullPointerException
        Sets the desired operating mode of the thermostat. There may be some delay before this change takes effect.
        Parameters:
        tmode - the new operating mode to set.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given operating mode is null

      • getFanMode

        FanMode getFanMode()
        Returns the current fan operating mode of the thermostat. This when the thermostat requests the fan to be on.
        Returns:
        the current fan operating mode. If this cannot be read, null will be returned.

      • setFanMode

        void setFanMode(FanMode fmode)
                throws NullPointerException
        Sets the desired fan operating mode of the thermostat. There may be some delay before this change takes effect.
        Parameters:
        fmode - the new fan operating mode to set
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given fan operating mode is null

      • getOverrideMode

        Boolean getOverrideMode()
        Get the status of the target temperature temporary override.
        Returns:
        true if override is enabled, false if it is disabled, and null if the current state cannot be determined.

      • getHoldStatus

        Boolean getHoldStatus()
        Get the target temperature hold status. If this is enabled, then any other thermostat programs will not engage. If disabled, then any temperature overrides will be removed when the next program starts.
        Returns:
        true if hold is enabled, false if it is disabled, and null if the current state cannot be dtermined.
        See Also:
        getOverrideMode()

      • setHoldStatus

        void setHoldStatus(Boolean hold)
                   throws NullPointerException
        Sets the current hold status.
        Parameters:
        hold - the hold status to set.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given hold status is null

      • getTemporaryHeatTarget

        Float getTemporaryHeatTarget()
        Gets the current temporary heat target.
        Returns:
        the current heat target, or null if the value cannot be determined.

      • setTemporaryHeatTarget

        void setTemporaryHeatTarget(Float t_heat)
                            throws NullPointerException
        Sets the current temporary heating target. If the operating mode is not currently OperatingMode.HEAT, then it will be set to that.
        Parameters:
        t_heat - the new temporary heat target to use
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given target temperature is null

      • getTemporaryCoolTarget

        Float getTemporaryCoolTarget()
        Gets the current temporary cooling target.
        Returns:
        the current cooling target, or null if the value cannot be determined.

      • setTemporaryCoolTarget

        void setTemporaryCoolTarget(Float t_cool)
                            throws NullPointerException
        Sets the current temporary cooling target. If the operating mode is not currently OperatingMode.COOL, then it will be set to that.
        Parameters:
        t_cool - the new temporary cooling target to use
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given target temperature is null

      • getThermostatState

        ThermostatState getThermostatState()
        Gets the current state of the thermostat (e.g. heating, cooling, off).
        Returns:
        the current thermostat state, or null if it cannot be determined.

      • getFanState

        Boolean getFanState()
        Gets the current state of the fan.
        Returns:
        true if the fan is on, false if the fan is off, and null if the current state cannot be determined.

      • getThermostatTime

        ThermostatTime getThermostatTime()
        Gets the current time, according to the thermostat.
        Returns:
        the current time, or null if it cannot be determined.

      • setThermostatTime

        void setThermostatTime(ThermostatTime time)
                       throws NullPointerException
        Sets the thermostat's time to the given time.
        Parameters:
        time - the time to set
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the give time is null

      • getThermostatModel

        String getThermostatModel()
        Gets the thermostat's model string.
        Returns:
        the thermostat's model, or null if it cannot be determined.

      • getSystemInfo

        SystemInfo getSystemInfo()
        Gets information about the thermostat system.
        Returns:
        thermostat system info, or null if it is not available.
